children.subject:
I got in this semester as a sophomore starting at 230th on waitlist because my enrollment time was decently late.
I think a lot more people behind me also got in.

P.S.: DS 189 hw's don't look easier to me, dunno about exams.

<md>cs189 (cdss) doesn't have easier anything -- it's the same class (in fact, the instructor has publicly claimed that they're using listgarten and malik's version of things). shewchuk semesters have the weeder hw in cs189 (eecs), but neither offering is necessarily easier or harder than the other.</md>

I got into 189 in sp21 as a sophomore. I think you still have a decent chance if you can do the weeder homework. A lot of people drop after the weeder hw and DS majors can just take the easier DS 189 version if they don't pass the regular weeder hw.

Enrollment priority is based on number of terms in attendance, showed on CalCentral. Summer does not count as a term I believe.

can't say anything about the fall but in shewchuk's 189 most (if not all) people get off the waitlist due to the super hard 2nd hw; a huge portion of the class drops after that hw is released, so as said previously, if you can make it through that hw then you'll be fine. also, when i took the class (a year ago) i was pretty intimidated by hw2, but they actually teach you most of the math material you need throughout the rest of the course, so don't be worried if you don't know all the concepts on hw2.

history.content: Hello! I will be a sophomore next year and am interested in taking 189 either in the fall (listgarten/Malik) or spring (shewchuk). Or is fall easier to guarantee enrollment in than spring, for example? Thanks!
